<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-08-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="3" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d3">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 3.</note>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Jay</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Fish</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-08"><hi rend="smallcaps">August 8, 1870.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Fish,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Secretary, Washington:</hi></p>
                        <p>Austria declines alliance proffered by France. War preparations and
                            fortifications continue, but only as precautionary and for defense.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>JAY.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>